  <exemplum>
    <p>If all that is desired is to call attention to the
fact that the copy text has been corrected, <gi>corr</gi> may be used alone:</p>
<egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">I don't know, Juan. It's so far in the past now &mdash;
how <corr>can we</corr><![CDATA[ prove or disprove anyone's theories?]]></egXML>
</exemplum>
  <exemplum><p>It is also possible to identify the individual
  responsible for the correction, and, using the <gi>choice</gi> and
  <gi>sic</gi> elements, to provide a correct reading:</p>
<egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">I don't know, Juan. It's so far in the past now &mdash;
how <choice><sic>we can</sic><corr resp="MSM">can we</corr></choice><![CDATA[ prove or
disprove anyone's theories?]]></egXML>
</exemplum>
<!-- <p>Note that order of elements within a <gi>choice</gi> element is
constrained: elements such as <gi>sic</gi> always precede elements
